This project is a RESTful API for managing products in a portfolio. It provides endpoints for CRUD operations on products.

Features
Get all products
Get a product by ID
Add a new product
Update an existing product
Delete a product

Technologies Used
ASP.NET Core
C#
.NET 9.0
OpenAPI (Swagger)

Getting Started
To get started with the Portfolio API, follow these steps:
Clone the repository: git clone https://github.com/iqbal30003/PORTFOLIOAPI.git
Restore the NuGet packages: dotnet restore
Build the project: dotnet build
Run the API: dotnet run

Endpoints
GET /products: Returns a list of all products.
GET /products/{id}: Returns a specific product by ID.
POST /products: Adds a new product.
PUT /products/{id}: Updates an existing product.
DELETE /products/{id}: Deletes a product.

Testing
The project includes a test file test.rest that provides examples of API requests and responses. You can use tools like Postman or cURL to test the API endpoints.